# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║ Security & Scanning Tools (installed via bootstrap.sh)      ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# The following tools are installed by bootstrap.sh as binaries and are
# not managed by mise. They are listed here for documentation purposes.
#
# Kubernetes Tools:
#   - krew (kubectl plugin manager)
#   - kubetail (multi-pod log tailing)
#   - popeye (cluster sanitizer)
#   - kube-capacity (resource analysis)
#
# Security Scanners:
#   - trivy (container & IaC security scanner)
#   - tfsec (Terraform security scanner)
#   - tflint (Terraform linter)
#
# Container Tools:
#   - dive (Docker image layer analyzer)
#
# CLI Tools:
#   - yq (YAML processor)
#
# Cloud Tools:
#   - aws-vault (secure AWS credential manager)
#
# To install these tools, run:
#   ./bootstrap.sh --full
#
# Or install individually via their respective package managers (brew, apt, etc.)
